        content: "If you see missing years or wrong amounts on your US earnings record, you can ask the Social Security Administration to correct them. The deadline is 3 years, 3 months, and 15 days from the date of the earnings, but exceptions allow corrections after the deadline if you have proof. Bring old W-2 forms, pay stubs, or tax returns to any Social Security office. You can also call 1-800-772-1213, which offers Spanish-language service. Ask for the Earnings Correction Department. The agent will open a case and tell you what proof to send. Common reasons for missing earnings include name changes after marriage, Social Security numbers entered incorrectly by an employer, and earnings paid in cash that an employer failed to report. The fix usually takes 4 to 6 months and adds the missing money to your record.",
