        content: "If you have at least 40 US credits, you can apply for retirement benefits as early as age 62, although your monthly payment is higher if you wait until age 67 or even 70. You can apply online at ssa.gov, by phone at 1-800-772-1213 with Spanish service, or in person at any Social Security office. The online application takes about 30 minutes. You will need your Social Security number, your date of birth, your bank account number for direct deposit, your most recent W-2 or self-employment tax return, and the names and birth dates of any current or former spouses. If you are not a US citizen but you are a lawful permanent resident, you can still receive benefits as long as you have the 40 credits. After you apply, the first payment usually arrives within 1 to 3 months.",
        tip: "Set up direct deposit to your US bank account during the application. The Social Security Administration no longer mails paper checks for new claims, and direct deposit is much safer than waiting for mail."
